<section>
<h2>1. Sage Agastya</h2>
<img src="https://mydattatreya.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/6-1.jpg" alt="Image of Sage Agastya">
<p>Sage Agastya is one of the most revered sages in Hindu tradition. He is known for his immense knowledge in various fields including astronomy, medicine, and philosophy. Agastya is credited with authoring several texts, including the Agastya Samhita, which contains information on various sciences and technologies.</p>
</section>

<section>
<h2>2. Sage Vasishtha</h2>
<img src="https://www.learnkriyayoga.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/Yoga-Vasistha-300x248.jpg" alt="Image of Sage Vasishtha">
<p>Sage Vasishtha is renowned for his contributions to Vedic literature and is considered one of the seven great sages (Saptarishi). He is known for his wisdom and is often associated with advanced knowledge of architecture and engineering, which is reflected in the construction of the mythical city of Ayodhya.</p>
</section>

<section>
<h2>3. Sage Patanjali</h2>
<img src="https://historified.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/b72af41e006b62a2ab9eb071d3cc8791-564x560.jpg.webp" alt="Image of Sage Patanjali">
<p>Sage Patanjali is best known for his work in yoga and linguistics. His text, the Yoga Sutras, lays the foundation for modern yoga practices and philosophy. He is also credited with the creation of the grammar rules that are still in use today, showcasing the technological advancement in linguistics in ancient India.</p>
</section>

<section>
<h2>4. Sage Kapila</h2>
<img src="https://divyakataksham.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/sage-kapila.jpg" alt="Image of Sage Kapila">
<p>Sage Kapila is recognized for his contributions to the philosophy of Sankhya and is often regarded as the father of this school of thought. His teachings emphasize the importance of understanding the universe and consciousness, which reflects a deep understanding of metaphysics and science.</p>
</section>

<section>
<h2>5. Sage Charaka</h2>
<img src="https://www.indica.today/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/history-of-ayurveda-640x394.jpg" alt="Image of Sage Charaka">
<p>Sage Charaka is considered the father of Ayurveda, the ancient Indian system of medicine. His work, the Charaka Samhita, is a comprehensive text that discusses various aspects of medicine, health, and wellness, showcasing the advanced medical knowledge of ancient India.</p>
</section>

